                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d284">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Rockhill</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.–Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-06-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 19, 1901</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Rockhill reports that the agreement reported in his telegram of the 11th
                    instant is imperiled by the British refusal to accept the proposal of France and
                    Russia that, in event of irregularity in making payments by China, the eventual
                    raising of the tariff to 10 per cent to supply deficiency be discussed; all the
                    powers to make all reservations they choose to whenever the discussion begins.
                    Mr. Rockhill hopes that British opposition can be overcome. None of the
                    ministers there can see danger in the proposal, which affords satisfaction to
                    Russia and France for relinquishing guaranteed loan in favor of bonds. * *
                    *)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
